\f0\fs24 \cf0 Your assignment is to write a job description for a position related to visual media. Refer to the reading assignment and the DVD that comes with the textbook for information to get you started. The book primarily focuses on visual media for entertainment and for corporate video projects. There are a host of other types of jobs that aren\'92t covered in the reading, like for video games or websites. \ \ You should include in your paper, but please don\'92t limit your paper to, the following: \ \ * A list of skills needed to complete the job (keep in mind we\'92re dealing with new media, web, video, etc.).\ * Qualifications\ * Salary Range\ \ Follow the general research paper format (introduction, body, conclusion, references). The textbook should not be your only resource. You will be graded according to how much additional research you\'92ve conducted outside of the reading assignment. If you get information from a website, be sure to include the link in your list of references.\ \ Turn in your paper electronically using the Assignments tool by the start of class on Monday, April 7th.\ }
